Goddy Egene The Board of Directors of MRS Oil Nigeria Plc has appointed Mr. Samson Adejonwo as the new chief finance officer (CFO) of the company to replace Mr. Charles Agutu. In a notification to the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE), the company commended Agutu, saying his proficiency, influenced the growth of the company during his tenure. The company noted that the new CFO, Adejonwo, has over 12 yearsâ€™ experience in Accounting and Management. He held various positions in organisations, such as Summit Finance Company, ALM Consulting Limited before joining MRS Holdings Limited. According to the company, he holds an MBA degree in International Business Management from Lagos State University and he is an Associate Member of the Institute of Chartered Accountant of Nigeria. Until his appointment as the Chief Finance Officer (CFO), he was the Finance Manager of MRS Oil and Gas Company Limited.